{"TopicId":25321,"ForumId":25,"TopicTitle":"Sun Escape Challenge! - demo only","CreatedByName":"EventHorizon","CreatedById":58240,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-05-03T21:09:58Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"EventHorizon","CreatedById":58240,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-05-03T21:09:58Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EOk so having landed on the mun i started playing around to see how far away from the sun i could get with the capsule. Not even sure if this is possible but using demo parts only (i.e. the demo) see if we can achieve a \u003Cstrong\u003E\u0022sun escape\u0022 \u003C/strong\u003Etrajectory.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EBest effort so far 167.6 million km. Which in the real solar system is a bit further out than Earth.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EPost your efforts in here.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://www.flickr.com/photos/93755067@N08/8704838433/sizes/h/in/photostream/\u0022 alt=\u0022photostream\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022http://www.flickr.com/photos/93755067@N08/8704838433/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttp://www.flickr.com/photos/93755067@N08/8704838433/\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EChallenge updated (as it was far to easy!) to \u003Cstrong\u003E\u0022Sun escape with fewest parts\u0022\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222013-05-03T22:38:56Z\u0022 title=\u002205/03/2013 10:38  PM\u0022 data-short=\u002211 yr\u0022\u003EMay 3, 2013\u003C/time\u003E by EventHorizon\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Giggleplex777","CreatedById":29829,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-05-03T22:02:33Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EThis is going to be very easy...\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EI\u0027ll post my entry soon.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EEdit: Done.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThis has to be the ugliest rocket I\u0027ve ever built.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/mKK1YKd.jpg\u0022 alt=\u0022mKK1YKd.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003ESolar escape:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/iYzojjE.png\u0022 alt=\u0022iYzojjE.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222013-05-03T22:14:12Z\u0022 title=\u002205/03/2013 10:14  PM\u0022 data-short=\u002211 yr\u0022\u003EMay 3, 2013\u003C/time\u003E by Giggleplex777\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Boex","CreatedById":19600,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-05-03T22:13:52Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003ESun escape is not particularly difficult, even with \u0022just demo parts\u0022. \u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EYou might want to alter this challenge to something like \u0022Sun Escape with Lowest parts\u0022 or \u0022Least fuel\u0022. \u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"EventHorizon","CreatedById":58240,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-05-03T22:37:36Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EWell done giggle. You can see im total noob at this. Yeah good idea box. Lets change it to \u003Cstrong\u003E\u0022Sun escape with fewest parts\u0022\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003Ebtw how do i embed pictures on here?\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222013-05-03T22:41:01Z\u0022 title=\u002205/03/2013 10:41  PM\u0022 data-short=\u002211 yr\u0022\u003EMay 3, 2013\u003C/time\u003E by EventHorizon\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Giggleplex777","CreatedById":29829,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-05-03T23:03:24Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022EventHorizon\u0022 data-cite=\u0022EventHorizon\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003EWell done giggle. You can see im total noob at this. Yeah good idea box. Lets change it to \u003Cstrong\u003E\u0022Sun escape with fewest parts\u0022\u003C/strong\u003E\u003Cp\u003Ebtw how do i embed pictures on here?\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003EYou can go to Forum\u0027s Settings -\u0026gt; General settings -\u0026gt; and change the \u0022Message Editor Interface\u0022 to Standard Editor (don\u0027t forget to click \u0022Save Changes\u0022!). When you post, click on the little picture box in the editor and paste the URL of your picture.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Nalin_Airheart","CreatedById":59462,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-05-04T01:16:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EHere\u0027s my entry, not really meant for the challenge but the serial staging testbed did get a pretty high apoapsis of 371MK up.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EHow are people escaping the sun at 4.5Km/s while my ship can\u0027t escape at 12.3Km/s?\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003ECraft File \u003Ca href=\u0022http://www./?14teyppc2wilyz2\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttp://www./?14teyppc2wilyz2\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe I-1 on Launchpad \u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022http://www.flickr.com/photos/95460760@N03/8705236125/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://farm9.staticflickr.com/8544/8705236125_8dd725579f.jpg\u0022 alt=\u00228705236125_8dd725579f.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022http://www.flickr.com/photos/95460760@N03/8705236125/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E2013-05-03_00005\u003C/a\u003E by \u003Ca href=\u0022http://www.flickr.com/people/95460760@N03/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003ENalin_Airheart\u003C/a\u003E, on Flickr\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003ENearing the last stage\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022http://www.flickr.com/photos/95460760@N03/8705236207/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://farm9.staticflickr.com/8257/8705236207_e49b86e6c9.jpg\u0022 alt=\u00228705236207_e49b86e6c9.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022http://www.flickr.com/photos/95460760@N03/8705236207/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E2013-05-03_00006\u003C/a\u003E by \u003Ca href=\u0022http://www.flickr.com/people/95460760@N03/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003ENalin_Airheart\u003C/a\u003E, on Flickr\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EFastest Speed\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022http://www.flickr.com/photos/95460760@N03/8705308613/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://farm9.staticflickr.com/8404/8705308613_277b9127b7.jpg\u0022 alt=\u00228705308613_277b9127b7.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022http://www.flickr.com/photos/95460760@N03/8705308613/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E2013-05-03_00012\u003C/a\u003E by \u003Ca href=\u0022http://www.flickr.com/people/95460760@N03/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003ENalin_Airheart\u003C/a\u003E, on Flickr\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EApoapsis\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022http://www.flickr.com/photos/95460760@N03/8706358152/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://farm9.staticflickr.com/8116/8706358152_e7c20a5f41.jpg\u0022 alt=\u00228706358152_e7c20a5f41.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022http://www.flickr.com/photos/95460760@N03/8706358152/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E2013-05-03_00013\u003C/a\u003E by \u003Ca href=\u0022http://www.flickr.com/people/95460760@N03/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003ENalin_Airheart\u003C/a\u003E, on Flickr\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EFlight Data\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022http://www.flickr.com/photos/95460760@N03/8705236387/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://farm9.staticflickr.com/8275/8705236387_e9e2c6f326.jpg\u0022 alt=\u00228705236387_e9e2c6f326.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022http://www.flickr.com/photos/95460760@N03/8705236387/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E2013-05-03_00014\u003C/a\u003E by \u003Ca href=\u0022http://www.flickr.com/people/95460760@N03/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003ENalin_Airheart\u003C/a\u003E, on Flickr\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222013-05-04T20:19:12Z\u0022 title=\u002205/04/2013 08:19  PM\u0022 data-short=\u002211 yr\u0022\u003EMay 4, 2013\u003C/time\u003E by Nalin_Airheart\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Francesco","CreatedById":58274,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-05-04T19:04:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E15 parts.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/ELcuPwV.jpg\u0022 alt=\u0022ELcuPwV.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/LeCf9Vc.png\u0022 alt=\u0022LeCf9Vc.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022http://imgur.com/a/N0T1B#0\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttp://imgur.com/a/N0T1B#0\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Giggleplex777","CreatedById":29829,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-05-05T23:29:32Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Nalin_Airheart\u0022 data-cite=\u0022Nalin_Airheart\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003EHere\u0027s my entry, not really meant for the challenge but the serial staging testbed did get a pretty high apoapsis of 371MK up.\u003Cp\u003EHow are people escaping the sun at 4.5Km/s while my ship can\u0027t escape at 12.3Km/s?\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003EYour speed is relative to the Sun, while my speed is relative to Kerbin.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"EventHorizon","CreatedById":58240,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-05-16T16:49:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EIm not sure that a dotted line counts?. Successful attempts must have that funny marker that says xxxx escape.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EIsn\u0027t solid blue line where you are going at the moment? So your actual trajectory? Not a fictional one.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EEdit: ive actualy done it. You dont get a sun escape marker so forget that, but you do get a solid blue line. So i dont think yours is valid francesco tbh.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022http://www.flickr.com/photos/93755067@N08/8745081014/in/photostream/lightbox/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttp://www.flickr.com/photos/93755067@N08/8745081014/in/photostream/lightbox/\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003Ehow do i embed an image on here?\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EAlso giggle yours is in orange so thats another fail. (isnt it?)\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222013-05-16T17:22:07Z\u0022 title=\u002205/16/2013 05:22  PM\u0022 data-short=\u002211 yr\u0022\u003EMay 16, 2013\u003C/time\u003E by EventHorizon\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"maltesh","CreatedById":17144,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-05-16T17:25:08Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003ENo, it isn\u0027t. It just means that he hasn\u0027t left the Kerbin sphere of influence yet. As you can see on the screenshot, he took it only 14 minutes after launch. A bit of time acceleration, and the orange line would turn blue.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Phaedrus2401","CreatedById":66458,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-05-16T18:35:52Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EHeh, well I won\u0027t be winning any awards for least parts or least fuel -- but I did manage to put a very, very large (and cool looking) probe into a solar escape trajectory.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EStage 1: 4x Mainsail \u002B Orange Fuel Tank (Boost)\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EStage 2: Mainsail \u002B 2x Orange Fuel Tank (Boost)\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EStage 3: LV-N Atomic Rocket Engine \u002B FL-T800 (Injection stage)\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EProbe: 5x Ion Thrusters, 8x Xenon Gas Tanks, 4x Z-400 Batteries, 4x Thermoisotopic Generators, 8x Gigantor XL Solar Panels \u002B Advanced SAS \u002B antennas and instruments and junk\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://fc07.deviantart.net/fs70/f/2013/136/e/6/star_goer_ia_booster_by_phaedrus2401-d65h53y.png\u0022 alt=\u0022star_goer_ia_booster_by_phaedrus2401-d65h53y.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EAnd holy crap a lot of struts. I had major wobble and stability issues at launch. I probably went overkill a little, but it didn\u0027t cost me too much delta-V.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EInjection Stage:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://fc07.deviantart.net/fs71/f/2013/136/3/f/star_goer_ia_by_phaedrus2401-d65h2z7.png\u0022 alt=\u0022star_goer_ia_by_phaedrus2401-d65h2z7.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EI followed the Voyager probe format, doing a slingshot around Jool, and getting very nice photos of Tylo, Vall, and especially Laythe as I went. Laythe screwed my orbit a bit, so I had to spend a lot of Xenon fuel to escape the Jool system; but I still ended up with enough left to escape the solar system.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://fc02.deviantart.net/fs70/f/2013/136/a/e/star_goer_ia_8_by_phaedrus2401-d65h323.png\u0022 alt=\u0022star_goer_ia_8_by_phaedrus2401-d65h323.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://fc06.deviantart.net/fs70/f/2013/136/8/0/star_goer_ia_17_by_phaedrus2401-d65h313.png\u0022 alt=\u0022star_goer_ia_17_by_phaedrus2401-d65h313.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://fc02.deviantart.net/fs71/f/2013/136/3/e/star_goer_ia_31_by_phaedrus2401-d65h2zc.png\u0022 alt=\u0022star_goer_ia_31_by_phaedrus2401-d65h2zc.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EA last look back at home.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://fc08.deviantart.net/fs70/f/2013/136/b/2/star_goer_ia_33_by_phaedrus2401-d65h53h.png\u0022 alt=\u0022star_goer_ia_33_by_phaedrus2401-d65h53h.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}